Call for participation – CLEF 2016 Workshop  - Cultural Microblog
Contextualization

Task 1 – guideline available

https://mc2.talne.eu/~cmc/spip/Tasks/cultural-multilingual-microblog-contextualization-based-on-wikipedia.html

To participate, register at:
http://clef2016-labs-registration.dei.unipd.it/
(free registration)

Important dates
----------------

23 May, 2016        Task 1 participation deadline
7 june, 2016        Participant paper submissions
5-8 September, 2016    CLEF conference, Évora, Portugal

This CLEF Workshop considers the smartphone as the main user interface.
This terminal can provide extra contextual information about its user
but has a reduced display. Therefore all outputs need to use reduce
display, give the essential information to better understand and fully
participate to an ongoing event or chose next cultural event to join.

Task 1 Objectives
This task aims at generating a short summary providing the background
information of a tweet to help a user to understand it. Given a
microblog announcing some cultural event, participants have to provide a
short summary extracted from Wikipedia that provides -extensive
-background about this event. The summary must contain some context
information about the event in order to help answering questions of the
form "what is this tweet about?" using a recent cleaned dump of
Wikipedia. The context should take the form of a readable summary, not
exceeding 500 words, composed of passages from the provided Wikipedia
corpus.

More details at
https://mc2.talne.eu/~cmc/spip/Tasks/cultural-multilingual-microblog-contextualization-based-on-wikipedia.html

